Implemented the check-cfg lint migration.

Changes made:
- Added `[lints.rust] unexpected_cfgs = { ..., check-cfg = [...] }` entries to relevant manifests:
  - `tokio/Cargo.toml`
  - `tokio-util/Cargo.toml`
  - `tokio-stream/Cargo.toml`
  - `tokio-test/Cargo.toml`
  - `tokio-macros/Cargo.toml`
  - `examples/Cargo.toml`
- Removed crate-level `#![allow(unknown_lints, unexpected_cfgs)]` workaround from non-test source files.
- Removed hidden doctest workaround lines in `tokio-macros/src/lib.rs`.
- Fixed one actual cfg typo caught by the lint:
  - `#[cfg_attr(not(fs), ...)]` → `#[cfg_attr(not(feature = "fs"), ...)]`

Validation run:
- `cargo check -p tokio --all-features`
- `cargo check -p tokio --tests --all-features`
- `cargo check -p tokio-util --all-features`
- `cargo check -p tokio-util --tests --all-features`
- `cargo check -p tokio-stream --all-features`
- `cargo check -p tokio-stream --tests --all-features`
- `cargo check -p examples --example dump`
- `cargo check -p tokio-macros`

Also ran `cargo test -p tokio-macros --doc`; it still has two pre-existing doctest failures around `start_paused`, unrelated to this change.
